<br>
A certain little girl, when asked her name, would reply, "I'm Mr. <br>
<br>
Sugarbrown's daughter." Her mother told her this was wrong, she <br>
<br>
must say,"I'm Janey Sugarbrown." The Vicar spoke to her in Sunday <br>
<br>
School, and said,"Aren't you Mr. Sugarbrown's daughter?" <br>
<br>
With her mother standing just a few feet away, the little girl <br>
<br>
replied, "I thought I was, but Mommy says I'm not." <br>
