<br>
A mother was teaching her 3-year-old the Lord's prayer. For several <br>
<br>
evenings at bedtime she repeated it after her mother. One night she <br>
<br>
said she was ready to solo. The mother listened with pride as she carefully <br>
<br>
enunciated each word, right up to the end of the prayer. "Lead us not <br>
<br>
into temptation," she prayed, "but deliver us some E-mail, Amen." <br>
<br>
